      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that \"predictive algorithm\" thing is literally just a polite way of saying they're reading my physiological signals to guess how i'm feeling. if the tech exists to pick up on heart rate or breathing through micro-vibrations or even just light changes, then why wouldn't they use it? it feels less like a \"glitch\" and more like they're running a live longitudinal study on my behavior. if a company wanted to see how humans react to certain environmental shifts in real time, wouldn't a smart home be the perfect, invisible lab for that?",
